description:
Continuing through our Lineage Journey, we learn about four men who were instrumental in the history of the Sabbath. Joseph Bates, T.M. Preble, Cyrus Farnsworth and Frederick Wheeler had a great impact on the adoption of the Sabbath by Advent believers. Three of them would meet in Washington, New Hampshire where their decision would be solidified through prayer and Bible study.

To find out more information about the Sabbath read our extended article on our website. 
https://lineagejourney.com/read/the-sabbath-pact-and-sabbath-conferences
